duck: American Independent Party - The American Independent Party is a right-wing political party of the United States that was established in 1967 by Bill and Eileen Shearer.
Acute intermittent porphyria - Acute intermittent porphyria (AIP) is a rare autosomal dominant metabolic disorder affecting the production of heme, the oxygen-binding prosthetic group of hemoglobin.

Air-independent propulsion - Air-independent propulsion is a term that encompasses technologies which allow a submarine to operate without the need to surface or use a snorkel to access atmospheric oxygen.
